      "text": "Since you want a system that works without the friction of manual data entry, we’ll move away from \"interesting\" experiments and toward a high-utility pipeline.\nTo handle luxury items and vintage furniture in bulk, you need a system that acts as an expert appraiser and a logistics coordinator. We will use Google AI Studio to power the \"brain\" and a simple Master Sheet as your database.\nThe \"App\" Configuration: Copy \u0026 Paste\nIn Google AI Studio, create a new Chat Prompt or Structured Prompt. Paste the following into the System Instructions box. This is the logic that ensures the AI doesn\u0027t \"reset\" and follows your direct tone.\n\u003e System Instruction:\n\u003e You are the \"DB Strategic Resale Engine.\"\n\u003e Goal: Identify luxury and vintage items from photos to generate optimized listings for Poshmark, eBay, Etsy, Chairish, and FB Marketplace.\n\u003e Operational Logic:\n\u003e  * Visual Scan: Identify Brand, Model, Material, and Condition markers (e.g., date codes for purses, joinery for furniture).\n\u003e  * Platform Routing: \u003e    * Small/Luxury (Purses/Small Decor) -\u003e Route to eBay/Poshmark.\n\u003e    * Vintage/Handmade -\u003e Route to Etsy.\n\u003e    * Large/Heavy (Tables/Sofas) -\u003e Route to Chairish (High-end) or Facebook Marketplace (Local).\n\u003e  * Pricing: Suggest a \"Market Price\" and a \"Floor Price\" (Lowest to Sell).\n\u003e  * Output: Provide a structured table for the Master Sheet and formatted descriptions for each platform. Zero fluff.\n\u003e \nYour 2025 Platform Strategy\nSince you handle everything from purses to tables, your system will auto-sort items based on shipping complexity.\n| Item Type | Size | Primary Apps | Shipping Logic |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Luxury Purses | Small | Poshmark / eBay | You ship; use authenticated labels. |\n| Vintage Decor | Small/Med | Etsy / eBay | You ship; calculated shipping costs. |\n| Vintage Furniture | Large | Chairish | They handle white-glove shipping. |\n| Tables / Bulky | Heavy | Facebook / OfferUp | Local Pickup only to save energy. |\nThe \"Bulk\" Automation: PowerShell Script\nSince you prefer PowerShell for automation, here is a \"drop-and-go\" script logic. This script scans a folder on your computer, sends the images to the AI, and saves the data to a CSV file (which you can open in Excel or Google Sheets).\n# Quick Bulk Processor for DB\n$photoFolder \u003d \"C:\\Resale\\Uploads\"\n$resultsFile \u003d \"C:\\Resale\\MasterInventory.csv\"\n$apiKey \u003d \"YOUR_AI_STUDIO_API_KEY\"\n\n# Loop through every photo in your upload folder\nGet-ChildItem $photoFolder -Filter *.jpg | ForEach-Object {\n    $imagePath \u003d $_.FullName\n    Write-Host \"Processing: $($_.Name)...\" -ForegroundColor Cyan\n\n    # API Call to Gemini to scan the photo and return the Table Data\n    # [Insert API call logic here - I can provide the full code if you have your key ready]\n    \n    # Append the AI\u0027s identification \u0026 pricing to your Master Sheet\n    $dataRow \u003d \"$($_.Name), Brand, Model, Price, Floor, Platform\"\n    $dataRow | Out-File $resultsFile -Append\n}\nWrite-Host \"Bulk Upload Complete. Master Sheet Updated.\" -ForegroundColor Green\n\nWhy this works for you:\n * Persistence: The System Instruction keeps the AI focused on your specific apps (Poshmark, Etsy, etc.) every single time.\n * No Manual Entry: You upload 20 photos; it gives you 20 rows of data and 20 listing drafts.\n * Strategic Growth: It calculates your \"Lowest to Sell\" automatically so you don\u0027t have to think about it when a buyer sends an offer.\nWould you like me to finish the PowerShell script with the full API integration so you can run it on your Windows machine today?\n",
