      "text": "**Constructing a Pipeline**\n\nI\u0027m currently focused on building a high-utility pipeline. My aim is to identify and list luxury and vintage items. I\u0027m leveraging Google AI Studio (Gemini) and a PowerShell script to automate the process. Thinking about item categories, I\u0027m considering luxury purses, vintage furniture, small decor, and bulky items for inclusion.\n\n\n**Developing API Integration**\n\nI\u0027ve been working on the API integration for Gemini. The PowerShell script is nearing completion. I\u0027ve successfully set up variables, encoded images using `[Convert]::ToBase64String`, and am now constructing the JSON body. The current focus is on the `gemini-1.5-flash` model, ensuring the prompt effectively extracts data from the image. The POST method and endpoint are now set.\n\n\n**Refining Script Functionality**\n\nI\u0027m now focusing on the final steps of the PowerShell script. Specifically, I\u0027m integrating `Invoke-RestMethod` to interface with Google\u0027s API, followed by parsing the JSON response. My goal is to extract the relevant text returned by the AI. To streamline the \"Master Sheet\" output, I\u0027m refining the prompt to elicit a single CSV line per item. I\u0027m also adding error handling and implementing the requested file naming conventions, while keeping the user\u0027s \"Zero fluff\" request in mind.\n\n\n",
