      "text": "This is a sophisticated approach to high-volume resale. By using **Gemini 1.5 Flash** (via the API), we can process these images rapidly and cheaply. The \"Flash\" model is specifically optimized for high-speed vision tasks like this.\n\nBelow is the complete PowerShell script. It includes the logic to **Base64 encode your images**, send them to the Google AI Studio API, and parse the response directly into your CSV.\n\n### Prerequisites\n1.  **API Key:** Get it from [Google AI Studio](https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey).\n2.  **Folder Setup:** Create `C:\\Resale\\Uploads` and put a few test `.jpg` files there.\n\n### The Full PowerShell Script\n\n```powershell\n# --- CONFIGURATION ---\n$apiKey \u003d \"YOUR_YOUR_API_KEY_HERE\"\n$photoFolder \u003d \"C:\\Resale\\Uploads\"\n$resultsFile \u003d \"C:\\Resale\\MasterInventory.csv\"\n\n# Create the CSV header if the file doesn\u0027t exist\nif (-not (Test-Path $resultsFile)) {\n    \"FileName,Brand,Model,MarketPrice,FloorPrice,PrimaryPlatform,ShippingLogic\" | Out-File $resultsFile -Encoding utf8\n}\n\n# --- SYSTEM PROMPT ---\n$systemPrompt \u003d @\"\nYou are the DB Strategic Resale Engine. Identify luxury/vintage items from photos.\nReturn ONLY a single line of comma-separated values (CSV format) for the item.\nOrder: Brand, Model, Market Price, Floor Price, Platform, Shipping Logic.\nPlatform Logic: \n- Small/Luxury -\u003e eBay/Poshmark\n- Vintage/Handmade -\u003e Etsy\n- Large/High-end -\u003e Chairish\n- Heavy/Bulky -\u003e FB Marketplace\nZero fluff. No markdown. No conversational text.\n\"@\n\n# --- PROCESSOR ---\nGet-ChildItem $photoFolder -Filter *.jpg | ForEach-Object {\n    $imagePath \u003d $_.FullName\n    Write-Host \"Analyzing: $($_.Name)...\" -ForegroundColor Cyan\n\n    try {\n        # 1. Convert Image to Base64\n        $fileBytes \u003d [System.IO.File]::ReadAllBytes($imagePath)\n        $base64Image \u003d [Convert]::ToBase64String($fileBytes)\n\n        # 2. Construct API Payload\n        $payload \u003d @{\n            contents \u003d @(\n                @{\n                    parts \u003d @(\n                        @{ text \u003d $systemPrompt },\n                        @{\n                            inline_data \u003d @{\n                                mime_type \u003d \"image/jpeg\"\n                                data \u003d $base64Image\n                            }\n                        }\n                    )\n                }\n            )\n        } | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 10\n\n        # 3. Call Google Gemini API\n        $apiUrl \u003d \"https://generativelanguage.googleapis.com/v1beta/models/gemini-1.5-flash:generateContent?key\u003d$apiKey\"\n        $response \u003d Invoke-RestMethod -Method Post -Uri $apiUrl -ContentType \"application/json\" -Body $payload\n\n        # 4. Extract Text and Append to CSV\n        $aiResult \u003d $response.candidates[0].content.parts[0].text.Trim()\n        \n        # Add the filename to the start of the row\n        $csvRow \u003d \"$($_.Name),$aiResult\"\n        $csvRow | Out-File $resultsFile -Append -Encoding utf8\n\n        Write-Host \"Success: $aiResult\" -ForegroundColor Green\n    }\n    catch {\n        Write-Host \"Error processing $($_.Name): $($_.Exception.Message)\" -ForegroundColor Red\n    }\n}\n\nWrite-Host \"`nFinished! Check $resultsFile for your listings.\" -ForegroundColor Yellow\n```\n\n### How to use this script:\n\n1.  **Open Notepad** (or VS Code).\n2.  **Paste the code** above.\n3.  **Replace** `YOUR_YOUR_API_KEY_HERE` with your actual key from AI Studio.\n4.  **Save the file** as `ResaleProcessor.ps1` on your desktop.\n5.  **Run it:** Right-click the file and select **\"Run with PowerShell.\"**\n\n### Why this specific setup is powerful for you:\n\n*   **Gemini 1.5 Flash Vision:** Unlike older OCR tools, this understands *context*. If it sees a \"Herman Miller\" logo on the underside of a chair, it knows that\u0027s a Chairish item, not a Facebook Marketplace item.\n*   **The \"CSV Only\" Constraint:** By forcing the AI to return *only* a comma-separated line, we skip the need for complex data cleaning. It goes straight from the photo to your spreadsheet.\n*   **Cost Efficiency:** Gemini 1.5 Flash has a massive free tier (up to 15 requests per minute and 1,500 requests per day for free at the time of writing), making this pipeline essentially free for a mid-sized resale operation.\n\n### Pro-Tip for your Master Sheet:\nIf you want the script to also generate the **Full Description** for the listing (not just the CSV row), let me know. I can modify it to save a `.txt` file for every photo that contains a pre-written, SEO-optimized description for the specific platform it chose.",
