        "text": "item**.\n\nIn high-volume resale, you usually take 3–5 photos of one item. If you run"
      }, {
        "text": " the previous script, you get 5 duplicate rows. To fix this, we are going to upgrade the \"Brain\" to use **"
      }, {
        "text": "Batch Vision Processing**. \n\nInstead of sending 1 photo at a time, we will send **all** photos in the folder"
      }, {
        "text": " at once. We will tell Gemini: *\"Look at these 20 photos. Group the ones that belong to the same item,"
      }, {
        "text": " and check my Master Sheet to make sure I haven\u0027t listed them before.\"*\n\n### The New \"Efficiency\""
      }, {
        "text": " Logic\n1.  **Image Grouping:** The AI identifies that Photo A, B, and C are all the same \"Louis"
      }, {
        "text": " Vuitton Speedy 30\" and merges them into one entry.\n2.  **Duplicate Detection:** The script reads your"
      }, {
        "text": " `MasterInventory.csv` first and sends the \"Already Owned\" list to the AI so it doesn\u0027t create"
      }, {
        "text": " doubles.\n3.  **JSON Output:** We move from CSV to JSON for the API response because it\u0027s"
      }, {
        "text": " much harder for the AI to \"break\" the formatting when handling multiple items.\n\n### Step 1: Updated System Instructions ("
      }, {
        "text": "Copy/Paste to AI Studio)\nReplace your previous instructions with these to enable \"Deduplication Mode\":\n\n\u003e You"
      }, {
        "text": " are the \"DB Strategic Resale Engine.\"\n\u003e **Task:** Analyze a batch of images and generate a consolidated inventory list.\n"
      }, {
        "text": "\u003e **Logic:** \n\u003e 1. **Grouping:** Multiple images may show the same item from different angles. Group them into"
      }, {
        "text": " a single unique ID.\n\u003e 2. **Deduplication:** I will provide a list of \"Existing Inventory"
      }, {
        "text": ".\" If a new photo matches an item already in the list, label it \"DUPLICATE\" and do not create"
      }, {
        "text": " a new entry.\n\u003e 3. **Platform Routing:** Use previous logic (Large -\u003e Chairish, Small -\u003e eBay"
      }, {
        "text": ", etc.).\n\u003e **Output Format:** Return ONLY a JSON array of objects with these keys: Brand, Model, Market"
      }, {
        "text": "Price, FloorPrice, Platform, Status (New/Duplicate).\n\n---\n\n### Step 2: The \"Batch"
      }, {
        "text": "\" PowerShell Script\nThis script is much more efficient. It bundles your images and talks to the AI once per batch.\n\n```powers"
      }, {
        "text": "hell\n# --- CONFIG ---\n$apiKey \u003d \"YOUR_API_KEY\"\n$photoFolder \u003d \"C:\\Res"
      }, {
        "text": "ale\\Uploads\"\n$resultsFile \u003d \"C:\\Resale\\MasterInventory.csv\"\n\n# "
      }, {
        "text": "1. Load Existing Inventory to prevent duplicates\n$existingInventory \u003d \"\"\nif (Test-Path $resultsFile) {\n"
      }, {
        "text": "    $existingInventory \u003d Import-Csv $resultsFile | Select-Object -Property Brand, Model | ConvertTo-Json"
      }, {
        "text": "\n}\n\n# 2. Prepare all images in the folder\n$imageParts \u003d @()\n$files \u003d Get-"
      }, {
        "text": "ChildItem $photoFolder -Filter *.jpg\nforeach ($file in $files) {\n    $bytes \u003d ["
      }, {
        "text": "System.IO.File]::ReadAllBytes($file.FullName)\n    $b64 \u003d [Convert]::ToBase"
      }, {
        "text": "64String($bytes)\n    $imageParts +\u003d @{\n        inline_data \u003d @{\n            mime_type"
      }, {
        "text": " \u003d \"image/jpeg\"\n            data \u003d $b64\n        }\n    }\n}\n\n#"
      }, {
        "text": " 3. Add the instructions and the \"Memory\" of existing items\n$promptText \u003d \"Group these images into unique"
      }, {
        "text": " items. Do not repeat items. Cross-reference with this existing inventory to avoid duplicates: $existingInventory\"\n$payload"
      }, {
        "text": "Contents \u003d @(\n    @{\n        parts \u003d $imageParts + @{ text \u003d $promptText }\n"
      }, {
        "text": "    }\n)\n\n$payload \u003d @{ contents \u003d $payloadContents } | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 1"
      }, {
        "text": "0\n\n# 4. Call Gemini 1.5 Flash (Optimized for Batch Vision)\nWrite-Host \"Analyzing"
      }, {
        "text": " batch of $($files.Count) photos...\" -ForegroundColor Cyan\n$apiUrl \u003d \"https://generativelanguage."
      }, {
        "text": "googleapis.com/v1beta/models/gemini-1.5-flash:generateContent?key\u003d$"
      }, {
        "text": "apiKey\"\n\ntry {\n    $response \u003d Invoke-RestMethod -Method Post -Uri $apiUrl -ContentType \""
      }, {
        "text": "application/json\" -Body $payload\n    \n    # Clean the AI output (removing markdown code blocks if present"
      }, {
        "text": ")\n    $rawJson \u003d $response.candidates[0].content.parts[0].text -replace \""
      }, {
        "text": "```json\", \"\" -replace \"```\", \"\"\n    $items \u003d $rawJson | ConvertFrom-Json\n\n"
      }, {
        "text": "    # 5. Append only NEW, Non-Duplicate items to the CSV\n    foreach ($item in $items) {"
      }, {
        "text": "\n        if ($item.Status -ne \"Duplicate\") {\n            $newRow \u003d [PSCustomObject]"
      }, {
        "text": "@{\n                Date \u003d (Get-Date -Format \"yyyy-MM-dd\")\n                Brand \u003d $item"
      }, {
        "text": ".Brand\n                Model \u003d $item.Model\n                Price \u003d $item.MarketPrice\n                Floor \u003d $"
      }, {
        "text": "item.FloorPrice\n                Platform \u003d $item.Platform\n            }\n            $newRow | Export-Csv $"
      }, {
        "text": "resultsFile -Append -NoTypeInformation\n            Write-Host \"Added: $($item.Brand) $($item.Model)\""
      }, {
        "text": " -ForegroundColor Green\n        } else {\n            Write-Host \"Skipped Duplicate: $($item.Brand)\" -ForegroundColor Yellow\n"
      }, {
        "text": "        }\n    }\n}\ncatch {\n    Write-Host \"Error: $($_.Exception.Message)\" -"
      }, {
        "text": "ForegroundColor Red\n}\n```\n\n### Why this is a major upgrade:\n\n1.  **Image Grouping:**"
      }, {
        "text": " If you take 4 photos of a West Elm Dining Table, the AI now sees all 4 at once. It realizes it"
      }, {
        "text": "\u0027s **one** item and gives you **one** row in your sheet.\n2.  **Memory:** By"
      }, {
        "text": " passing `$existingInventory` into the prompt, the AI \"remembers\" what you\u0027ve already processed in previous runs"
      }, {
        "text": ".\n3.  **Speed:** Calling the API once for 10 images is significantly faster (and uses less of"
      }, {
        "text": " your rate limit) than calling it 10 times for 1 image each.\n4.  **Cleaner Data:** The JSON"
      }, {
        "text": "-to-CSV conversion ensures that commas in descriptions don\u0027t break your Excel columns.\n\n### Recommendation for \"Ultimate"
      }, {
        "text": "\" Efficiency:\nIf you are doing this in **bulk** (e.g., 50+ items at a time),"
      }, {
        "text": " move your photos into \"Batch Folders\" (Batch1, Batch2). Run the script on one folder, verify"
      }, {
        "text": " the results, and move to the next. This prevents the API from timing out on massive image sets."
      }, {
        "text": "",
        "thoughtSignature": ""
      }]
    }],
    "pendingInputs": [{
      "text": "",
      "role": "user"
    }]
  }
}